  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2004-10-08",
    "date": "2004-12-08T16:31:52Z",
    "text": "Green Chemistry Research and Development Act of 2004 - Directs the President to establish a Green Chemistry Research and Development Program to promote and coordinate Federal research, development, demonstration, education, and technology transfer activities related to green chemistry and chemical engineering to design chemical products and processes that reduce or eliminate the use or generation of hazardous substances.\n\nRequires the President to establish an Interagency Working Group to oversee the planning, management, and coordination of the Program."
